<div class="title">
==Description==
</div>
{{Blurimage|file=Level Skyscraper Bg.jpg|caption=An image of Foggy Skyscrapers taken in a helicopter.|align=right}}
Level 270, colloquially designated Foggy Skyscrapers, is a level consisting of thousands of millions of skyscrapers covered by a layer of fog. It appears to have modern buildings with different styles and heights, aligning densely across streets and paths. Lights are dazzling, bright and are constantly illuminated. The low visibility in this level hinders observation and investigations, as natural wind is unable to blow any fog vapor away due to its special properties which adhere to structures nearby and maintain their shapes firmly. Wanderers are not able to see the top of buildings from the ground, nor objects that are too far away from them (>500m). Currently, no studies have been conducted to formally investigate the full composition of this fog vapor as not many wanderers have visited this level, but preliminary analysis suggests the existence of ammonium as one component.

{{Blurimage|caption=An image taken during the daytime.|file=Level Skyscraper Daytime.jpg|align=right}}
This level has a long night and very short daytime, resulting in the phenomenon that most of the time, the level is dark. Sunlight appears on rare occasions; only one wanderer reported that they saw sunlight here. This makes electricity generation by solar power almost impossible here. However, electricity is available, supplying energy to light up the city. Wanderers may obtain electricity to charge their devices through any sockets in buildings or rooms. Numerous worn-out parts at this level have been found, where the lights or electricity do not work properly. Short circuits and lack of lighting might be found in these areas due to the fact that these facilities lack maintenance.   

Not much other information is available currently. However, a diary report by ''J.D. Thomas'' in a book called ''Exploring Skyscrapers'' may help illustrate one's experience and visit to this level. This article existed in the system as the file "File 01.docx" with no information revealing the author's identity. It is believed that special technologies were used to access the network and insert the document, most likely done at the level itself. This is mainly due to the fact that this level is claimed to have internet connection from 1980s computer-like electronic devices. Putting the question of why and how these devices can produce abnormally rapid switching and data transmission aside, scientists are more interested in how this level has such a continuous energy supply to light up all of its lights without fatigue or any wear and tear. The most logical theory is that this level has the ability to obtain enough energy from the sun during its daytime and also store enough energy to ensure its consumption at night. Others believe that the lights turn off and the electricity supply is cut when there are no wanderers in this level, and the supply returns to normal once someone steps into this level.   

====Wandering alone====
Once someone steps into this level, the appearance of this level will most likely change to fit the wanderer's idea of "urban", "city" and "skyscrapers". Multiple wanderers are allowed to enter this level concurrently, but they will then be separated into different dimensions with different networks of roads, time and initial positions. The feeling of isolation is often believed to be negligible, but they will soon find themselves becoming extremely depressed and unable to control their thoughts from turning dark. The appearance of this level, which is mostly dark grey or dark-colored even in the daytime, may exert an automatic response by the cerebrum to produce the interception of loneliness. However, wanderers have no escape from this situation and their only solution is to find the exit of this level, which is almost impossible. They will never hear any sound made by living things from the moment they step over a random door or suddenly clip in. As described by ''J.D. Thomas'', this is the "fear of being devoid of entities".   

According to a record sent from an anonymous wanderer, he mentioned that birds are found in a park next to a tall building covered by metal dyed white, on a tree. He also sent us a photo showing birds standing on the branches. This was later proven real, but only happens in very rare circumstances when this level accidentally connects to the wanderer's mind while it is the beginning of the daytime (this phase of the day cycle at this level is also called "morning"). Besides birds, a wanderer also mentioned that he saw tall entities pretending to be light poles in the daytime moving between streets. However, this was later falsified since it is too similar to fictional content created by an artist staying at [[Level 99]] called ''Joseph L.''.         

Since July 2007, there have been a total of 26 wanderers who have explored this level, with 2 that escaped from it. Others were reported missing and then certified dead after they could not be contacted for 3 months. Some wanderers attempted to find missing teammates in this level but most of them failed to come back. Now, Backrooms professionals suggest that the actual number of missing people should be far beyond the number in the record. One reason is that this level is "too easy to enter". Entrances exist in almost all levels in the Backrooms, making entrance to this level nothing more than a matter of probability. This feature is claimed to be caused by the continuous power supply discussed previously.                  

====City Climate====
When one arrives at this level, an obvious feature that can be noticed is the thick layer of fog in the sky. It is observed that this special kind of fog always locates at the middle level of the buildings. The fog layer blocks most of the light passing through it, which makes the estimation of the heights of the buildings solely reliant on mechanical estimation rather than physical calculations. Another characteristic is that this layer of fog remains a constant shape. Despite its gaseous state, particles in the fog layer maintain their distances from each other constantly, which holds its shape firmly. When the sun rises, this layer of fog does not evaporate and disappear since it is made up of fine solid particles with extremely high boiling points, similar to dust but with a much smaller particle size. This fog is found to consist of ammonium compounds in a shape similar to carbon flake pollutants. This substance causes no negative effect on humans' physiologic responses or balances, except that humans may experience unknown psychological changes such as suddenly becoming down or depressed after breathing in this vapor for more than 48 hours. Many possible effects of fog remain unconfirmed; with the account by ''J.D. Thomas'' providing the only case study, it is only certain that some of the many consequences include self-harm ideation, emotional changes and mind fog. 

The sensation of natural wind is only produced as a psychosomatic effect. One may clearly feel the breeze come from the end of the streets or the gaps between buildings and trees. However, native objects and dazzling debris are not affected by the breeze. On objects belonging to this level, no effect will be exerted. The air temperature at this level automatically adjusts once a human enters, to be a bit cooler than their optimal temperature. This induces a vague sense of unease or melancholy, together with the effect of the natural breeze. The air temperature stays constant during both daytime and nighttime. 

As this level is always covered by a thick layer of fog, it fails to receive enough sunlight even in the daytime. Trees appear to have serious chlorosis problems and falling leaves due to the bad quality of potassium-rich dirt. 

====Surviving in Skyscrapers====
For wanderers, survival becomes the largest problem due to the lack of methods for exiting and the potential mental problems caused by the special properties at this level that cannot be solved by drinking almond water. By receiving information from various records, it is concluded that the areas at this level can be divided into a few major parts.
<tabber>
|-|The Roads=
At the moment when one is brought to this level, they first appear on a road, most likely one intended for cars. This creates an illusion of having arrived in reality. The road could be a road that the wanderer walked frequently in the past, or one they didn't pay attention to. Their first emotion is excitement, but they will soon notice that the cars are not moving and no other humans are walking on sidewalks or inside stores, bringing them back to the Backrooms.
{{Blurimage|file=fog-road.png|caption=A road covered by fog.}}
Roads at this level are mostly made of concrete, but there might also be a small chance that dirt roads or roads surrounded by grass will be found. This is mainly because the wanderer's memories of the city they lived in have these kinds of roads. One common point about the roads is that the visibility on them is very low, with a maximum of 500m. Beyond that distance, nothing including the lines or the color of the road surface can be seen since they are blurred by the thick fog layer, even though the fog layer is mainly located around 25-75m high. Scientists believed it could be an illusion affecting the human eye. However, the existence of similar visual effects on camera results suggests that such a phenomenon is a physical change rather than an interceptional error. Some researchers mentioned that the fog near the wanderer is relatively thinner than that far away, and the foggy effect gets more serious when the distance increases, accounting for the low visibility.
|-|Parks=
Parks are common areas at this level. They are most likely, but not always, in the form of an "endless" park. Distinct characteristics of parks include large areas of grassland or long footpaths with wooden benches alongside. No potential threats have been discovered in parks. Most likely, wanderers will walk into parks when they discover them due to curiosity, and most likely they will sleep and rest on the benches. All wanderers who have done so remained lost, according to documented reports. It is uncertain whether there are any negative effects of sleeping and resting in the parks. Some wanderers also reported that trees at this level have a special odor, especially the cut ones. The smell is "perfume-like" with a milky texture and rose fragrance, according to all wanderers. Some scientists theorized that the substance produced by the trees will paralyze nerves and thus calm one down so that their thoughts become clearer, which makes them ponder, or even question, themselves. The cold architectural style with no warm feeling in this level intensifies the effect.
|-|Stores=
Wanderers may obtain daily necessities such as basic food, personal hygiene equipment or simple survival aids via convenience stores randomly scattered around the metropolis. Nevertheless, these convenience stores each have unique characteristics of their own and preserve the linkage between the metropolis and the Backrooms. For instance, a wanderer discovered objects that could be found in [[Level 1]], [[Level 2]] and [[Level 0]] in a convenience store located at a darker street corner. Described as "having an atmosphere completely standing out from this metropolis", convenience stores' safety is still a concern among wanderers. Many wanderers recommend not visiting any convenience stores, especially if one arrived at this level via no-clipping, due to the fact that these wanderers are more prone to the threats caused by randomness and possible errors occurring inside the stores. 
|-|Small Buildings=
There are numerous houses along the roads in the city, each with its own style, resembling wanderers' living areas in real life. These houses all have one thing in common - all the main doors of these buildings are identical black metal doors with traditional classic floral or decorative lines. These doors are all locked from the inside, and all houses have their lights off. No previous exploration records have been received.
|-|The Ultimate Skyscraper=
In the city, there is always one skyscraper that stands out from others, named "The Ultimate Skyscraper" among wanderers. It has the tallest height, and its lights have the strongest intensity. Wanderers theorized that such characteristics of lights and heights are an attraction for wanderers to enter. The "Ultimate Skyscraper" can be in any style, depending on the wanderer's definition of "Metropolis". It is much easier for a wanderer who is used to rural, countryside lifestyles to see skyscrapers as much more stunning and eye-catching than others. In spite of the reflecting glass windows and the lights, it has been proven that the skyscraper exists in an imaginary form with no substantial surfaces. It is an illusion created by the combined effect of the ammonium flakes inside the fog and a phenomenon called material agglutination, where loose flakes in the atmosphere clump to provide temporary surfaces. While one can walk inside the skyscraper, they are actually walking on components of the atmosphere or surfaces of random electronic-driven machines. Elevators are present inside the skyscraper to allow travel between floors, but these elevators do not allow control of destination. Even though wanderers believe that they selected a floor and were moved to a correct place, such movement is automatic and stereotyped in wanderers' minds and could never be changed. (i.e. The arrival of the same person at this level, even if they chose a different floor, the place that they arrive at will be the same, despite their own beliefs.) 
|-|Path Towards Death=
The following is an excerpt from the book Exploring Skyscrapers, where wanderer J.D. Thomas recorded a special characteristic - Path Towards Death
''Since the time you entered this level, everything is under control. You might find yourself having moments of tranquility, exploring freely inside this giant metropolis full of advanced skyscrapers. However, everything is delusional. Everything is a <b>path towards death</b>. You are being led to the Ultimate Skyscraper, which you might not even notice. The elevator door opens, you selected a floor. Everything is fake. No matter which floor you choose, the elevator is a blind end; it is a one-way journey from the bottom to the top. You will find yourself gradually losing your body weight; your limbs are lighter and you have the wrong impression that you are relaxed, carefree and enjoying yourself. The elevator, no matter where it goes along the journey, always leads you to the top of the building. This is a place where you are surrounded by extremely soothing, mildly cool, comfortable breeze. You will then look down at the metropolis, endless lights dazzling. A voice may appear deep inside your mind, asking if you want to fall into the lights. You may somehow, without notice, fall from the skyscraper directly down into the fog and clouds. Then, you will find yourself waking up at this level, as if this has never occurred.''
</tabber>

====Exploring Skyscrapers by ''J.D. Thomas''====
