<p><b>Welcome, <span class="insertusername">{{USERNAME}}</span>.</b><br>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}[File 01.docx]{{Image Banner|image=Skyscraper img 01.jpg|caption=You arrived, standing between skyscrapers that go above the clouds.}}"Where is here?" you asked yourself. This place looks almost identical to where you are from—a place full of skyscrapers, vehicles, and dazzling lights. You found yourself standing on a sidewalk in the middle of the carriageway. You walked back to the sidewalk subconsciously, afraid that you had blocked the cars' passage. When you were finally able to look at this place thoroughly, you noticed something: no one is walking here; not even a single person exists. Stores, banks, parks... You tried to find a car to see if there was a driver. At this moment, you finally spotted that cars were staying still on the roads, even though their lights were switched on.


You walked on the road, wandering around this place, trying to understand what was going on. Looking up, skyscrapers were so tall that you were unable to see the top. You could barely see lights on the walls illuminating the clouds, giving them blue, yellow, and violet colors. Skyscrapers, which appeared normal to you in the past, were something new to you. You found this place so familiar. It looks almost exactly the same as the place you lived before entering this hell. "Beep," your contact device buzzed, notifying you of new messages. You found a member of your wanderer group saying, "I escaped!" with a photo showing streets with skyscrapers along them. You knew who he was, of course. He is your friend who grew up with you. The photo showed the same scene you were looking at. You replied immediately, "Stay still!" and then rushed to the place where this photo was taken. What you saw is an empty alley; there is nothing here except trash. You realized that these levels seem independent of each other, and the appearances seen by different people are different. You confirmed the situation with your teammates and proved your claim. Now, you understand that you are alone here, and you must get out of here by yourself.


You heard a voice saying, "Why do you want to leave?"
{{Blurimage|file=Park Skyscraper.jpg|caption=Still remember here?|align=right}}Walking on the street, you found the lights were all on. That made you curious about the energy source of this level. In spite of the fact that no one is here, the lights are on to make this place warm, a kind of mental warmth. Seeing the street lights, you felt a calming sensation. From rushing, to slowly running, and then finally walking slowly and relaxingly on the street. Taking a deep breath, you felt much better. You took off all the armor on your body, feeling that your body was much lighter than before. You loved this place, a place with no conflicts, no evil, no noise, but only peace and silence. The fog at the end of the streets, covering everything in a dark mist, gave a feeling of mystery to this place. You did not care about what was behind the fog, though. Effortlessly, you found a small park hidden between skyscrapers, sat down, and immersed yourself in this beautiful city. You remembered when you were just a child. You loved it here.

Stay calm, take a break... Your journey still has a long way to go.{{Underline|FFFFFF}}{{Image Banner|image=Convenient-store Skyscrapers.png|caption=Suddenly, you felt starving.}}Walking out from the park, you felt relaxed. Throughout your exploration, you didn't find any entities here, as far as it seemed to be. You exited the park from the entrance. "So strange..." you mumbled "This isn't the street I came from..." You saw a convenience store, lights on, just no one there. It looked larger than the one in your old memories, or at least it felt like so. You felt a bit hungry after a walk, so you entered the store. At the moment you stepped into the store, yellow lights shone on your body. The lights in this city seemed to be brighter than ordinary cities, with very few dim lights and almost no lights that had gone off. You were at the cashier.

You knew what you wanted to do. Opening the drawer under the counter, what you saw was unexpected. A bottle of almond water, lying silently in the drawer, where treasure should belong. The machines' monitors were displaying the word "Welcome!", looking like waving hands towards this new visitor arriving at the dream land of technology, modernity and bustle. Just one thing, you were alone. You found a hot dog in a fridge. Cold and dry, you swallowed it. It tasted like the ones in reality, which brought back memories of reality, especially of the past decades. "This taste is familiar..." You felt tears in your eyes for no reason, and you wanted to cry. You knew what you had experienced, you knew what you were going to face. This is heaven. 

You felt a sense of fullness and satisfaction. Your teammates were calling you through the walkie-talkie, but you refused their connection requests.
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}{{Image Banner|caption=I would like to fall into the clouds.|image=Skyscraper Seamless.jpg}}
A feeling rose from your mind.

You entered the central building of this city. You walked into the elevator and pressed the button "100". As soon as the door closed, you were lifted up. This was followed by 50 seconds of silence.

The door opened and you walked out of it. You arrived at an office hall. The computers were arranged five in a row across the whole room. Each space was separated by a piece of thin wooden wall. "I will have to face this when I go back! But I won't go back anyway...!" you spoke.

"No one will know what I faced here!"

You stepped across the office hall and arrived at a door. Gently pushing, you saw a staircase. This seemed to be the staircase of the building. It seemed to be where you wanted to go; your eyes showed a bit of perseverance. You stepped up the staircase. Your footsteps echoed in the staircase, becoming loud and clear. 

Walking up to the end of the staircase and pushing open a door, you felt a strong wind. You were at the rooftop. No one, nothing here. You sat on the edge of the rooftop, looking at the city. Everything was covered by thick fog. You barely saw the ground, but you could see lights seeping through the clouds and making the clouds different colors. 

You just sat there, as the wind made your shirt swing. The wind was as soft as a bed. Time flew, slowly, with your thoughts. You thought of your experiences, your future, and this moment. You wanted to fall into the clouds. See how soft it is?

Abruptly, you seemed to have made up your mind.

Followed by a push from yourself, a strong sense of weightlessness arrived, but you didn't feel afraid. 

The skyscrapers started to become blurred, and you knew you were saying goodbye to them, and to yourself.

Lying on the bed of wind, you fell asleep slowly. You knew you would never wake up.

Have a good dream....
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}{{Image Banner|caption=Wait... This is where I started.|image=Office skyscrapers.jpg}}
Wait...

You woke up.

It all returned to where it started.

-The Book "''Exploring Skyscrapers''" Pages 1-4

=====Note:=====
The parts afterwards focus on imagination about this level and other suspected records, which contain unreliable sources of data.
